        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50562",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In the JSON string {{ZEND_CONFIG_JSON_ENV_INT}} is not surrounded by double-quotes like the others:\r\n{code}\r\n$json = '{\"env\":\"ZEND_CONFIG_JSON_ENV\",\"path\":\"ZEND_CONFIG_JSON_ENV_PATH\/tests\",\"int\":ZEND_CONFIG_JSON_ENV_INT}';\r\n{code}\r\nWhen I use [phpsh|http:\/\/www.phpsh.org\/] with 5.3.10 on RHEL to decode that string I get the message you are receiving:\r\n{code}\r\nphp> echo Zend_Json::decode( '{\"env\":\"ZEND_CONFIG_JSON_ENV\",\"path\":\"ZEND_CONFIG_JSON_ENV_PATH\/tests\",\"int\":ZEND_CONFIG_JSON_ENV_INT}');\r\nUncaught exception: Zend_Json_Exception: Decoding failed: Syntax error\r\n{code}\r\nHowever, when I run the unit tests on the same system I get all green:\r\n{code}\r\n$ phpunit34 Zend\/Config\/JsonTest.php\r\nPHPUnit 3.4.15 by Sebastian Bergmann.\r\n......................\r\nTime: 1 second, Memory: 8.25Mb\r\nOK (22 tests, 61 assertions)\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIt appears, then, to be an issue with PHP's {{json_decode}} function\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-09T16:44:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-09T16:44:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50578",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem is, that on Windows, the directory constant contains backslashes. After replacement it produces invalid JSON (backslashes must be escaped as \\\\\\)\r\n{code}{\"env\":\"testing\",\"path\":\"I:\\xampp\\zf\\tests\\Zend\\Config\/tests\",\"int\":42}{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-10T18:56:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-10T18:56:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50579",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Attaching patch, that add escaping of backslashes in PHP constats.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-10T18:56:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-10T18:56:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50580",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Your second snippet fails, because it replaces the constants, but they are not defined there. So it tries to parse invalid JSON.",
